│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The crash is an assertion failure within the SLP Vectorizer pass (`-O2` enables it). The   │
│ assertion `isa<Instruction>(Val)` fails inside `llvm::cast<Instruction>(Val)`, indicating  │
│ that the code is attempting to cast a `llvm::Value*` to a `llvm::Instruction*`, but the    │
│ `Value` is not an `Instruction`. This typically happens when the `Value` is a `Constant`,  │
│ `Argument`, or another non-instruction subclass of `Value`.                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `opt` debug log for SLP shows that the vectorizer is attempting to build a             │
│ vectorization tree. The log shows:                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ SLP: added a new TreeEntry (SelectInst/UnaryOperator/BinaryOperator/FreezeInst).           │
│ 2.                                                                                         │
